<LegalLayout
  title="Fulfillment Policy"
  description="How Revvia delivers its services, plus billing, refunds, and cancellation terms."
  path="/fulfillment"
>
  <p>This policy describes how Revvia (First Door, LLC) delivers and bills for its services. It exists in part to satisfy payment-processor requirements.</p>

  <h2>What we provide</h2>
  <p>Revvia provides marketing and growth services — paid media management, creative and in-house production, email and SMS retention, tracking and measurement, and related consulting — for consumer & lifestyle brands.</p>

  <h2>Service delivery</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Services are delivered digitally and through scheduled production days. Timelines are defined in your engagement agreement.</li>
    <li>Most retainers begin within one to two weeks of signing, after onboarding and access are complete.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Billing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Retainers are billed monthly in advance. Ad spend is billed directly to the client's own ad accounts unless otherwise agreed.</li>
    <li>Project and production work is billed per the project agreement.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cancellation &amp; refunds</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Engagements are month-to-month and may be cancelled with written notice as defined in your agreement.</li>
    <li>Because services are rendered as labor and media management, fees for work already performed are non-refundable. Any disputes are handled case by case — reach out and we'll make it right.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about fulfillment or billing? Email <a href="mailto:info@revvia.com">info@revvia.com</a> or call <a href="tel:+17607822875">(760) 782-2875</a>.</p>
</LegalLayout>
